What is awscli
--------------
--------------

awscli is an command line interface tool using which you can interact and manage 
multiple aws services from the commandline


Install awscli
---------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------



apt install awscli    ( on ubuntu)


yum install awscli ( on centos, AmazonLinux, Redhat)




    
List s3 buckets
------------------------------------------------------------


aws s3 ls



List the contents of particular s3 bucket
---------------------------------------------------------------


aws s3 ls s3://bucketname

eg: aws s3 ls s3://sep16



To Copy the File from S3 Bucket to EC2
----------------------------------------------------------------


aws s3 cp s3://bucketname/testfile.txt .

eg: aws s3 cp s3://sep16/becomedevopskubernetesresorces.PNG .

Note: . Dot downloads the objects in current directory


To Copy the files from EC2 to S3 bucket
----------------------------------------------------------------



aws s3 cp ec2-to-s3 s3://sep16/

   

